<item>Financial accounting reports are typically general-purpose reports.</item>
<item>Financial accounting reports pertain to the entity as a whole, whereas managerial accounting focuses more on subunits of the organization.</item>
<item>The main users of the financial accounting information are the internal users.</item>
<item>Managerial reports are prepared on an as-needed basis.</item>
<item>Financial accounting reports often must be audited at least annually by an independent auditor.</item>
